<subSubSection id="92D5D8D48F19FFF3FF30F862FC110DEF" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="550" pageId="10" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DA708B5F8F19FFF4FF30F862FD9E0C0B" blockId="10.[151,1437,1945,2043]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="10" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F19FFF5FF30F862FE900AA5" bold="true" box="[151,267,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="548">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F19FFF5FEB5F862FE790AA2" author="Maldonado, J." box="[274,482,1945,1972]" pageId="10" pageNumber="548" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
did not include 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F19FFF5FD31F862FC7B0AA5" authority="Breddin, 1904" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[662,992,1945,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F19FFF5FD31F862FCA10AA5" box="[662,826,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="548">C. nigriventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F19FFF5FCE7F862FC7B0AA5" author="Breddin, G." box="[832,992,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="548" pagination="147 - 148" refId="ref15054" refString="Breddin, G. (1904) Neue Rhynchotenausbeute aus Sud-Amerika. Societas Entomologica, 20, 147 - 148 + 153 - 154 + 177 - 178. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 9279381" type="journal article" year="1904">
Breddin, 
<quantity id="1D3726BA8F19FFF5FC0FF862FC7B0AA5" box="[936,992,1945,1971]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.83616" pageId="10" pageNumber="548" unit="in" value="1904.0">1904</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in his key or in his taxon treatment section. He stated that Breddin’s 
<typeStatus id="057435FD8F19FFF5FE4FF846FDD10AC1" box="[488,586,1981,2007]" pageId="10" pageNumber="548">holotype</typeStatus>
seems to be lost, and apparently was not at the DEI. We recently contacted Dr. S. Blank (DEI) and he confirmed that Breddin’s type is not there. We also contacted Dr. M. Husemann (ZMUH) who stated as well that Breddin’s type is not there, so apparently Breddin’s type could be lost. Alternatively, Dr. Blank indicated that it might still be possible for Breddin’s type to be unlabeled as a type and be sitting along his undetermined material, as has been the case with other Breddin type material. Unfortunately, so far, we have not been able to find such specimen.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8EB0DBD78F18FFF4FF30F9FCFADE0B55" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556788" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5556788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556788/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" startId="11.[151,250,1543,1567]" targetBox="[166,1435,309,1487]" targetPageId="11">
