type specimens. 
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FD1FF9FCFD4A0B09" bold="true" box="[696,721,1543,1567]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">A.</emphasis>
holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FCF7F9FCFB340B09" authority="Maldonado, 1976" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[848,1199,1543,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FCF7F9FCFC6C0B09" box="[848,1015,1543,1567]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">Castolus bicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FC5AF9FCFB340B09" author="Maldonado, J." box="[1021,1199,1543,1567]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FA9DF9F3FEF60B55" authority="Breddin, 1904" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FA9DF9F3FF4A0B55" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. nigriventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FF70F9D0FEF60B55" author="Breddin, G." box="[215,365,1579,1603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="147 - 148" refId="ref15054" refString="Breddin, G. (1904) Neue Rhynchotenausbeute aus Sud-Amerika. Societas Entomologica, 20, 147 - 148 + 153 - 154 + 177 - 178. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 9279381" type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FED9F9D0FE0E0B55" bold="true" box="[382,405,1579,1603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">B.</emphasis>
holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FDB1F9D7FCA10B55" authority="Brailovsky, 1982" authorityName="Brailovsky" authorityYear="1982" box="[534,826,1579,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivari">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FDB1F9D7FD1F0B55" box="[534,644,1579,1603]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. bolivari</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FD2DF9D0FCA10B55" author="Brailovsky, H." box="[650,826,1579,1603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="223 - 229" refId="ref15001" refString="Brailovsky, H. (1982) Hemiptera-Heteroptera de Mexico: XX. Notas acerca del genero Castolus Stal, y descripcion de una nueva especie. (Reduviidae-Harpactorinae). Anales del Instituto de Biologia de la Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Serie Zoologia, 1, 223 - 229." type="journal article" year="1982">Brailovsky, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FCE3F9D0FCC60B55" bold="true" box="[836,861,1579,1603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C.</emphasis>
holotype labels of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FBB8F9D7FAA40B55" authority="Maldonado, 1976" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[1055,1343,1579,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FBB8F9D7FB1D0B55" box="[1055,1158,1579,1603]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. bicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FB2BF9D0FAA40B55" author="Maldonado, J." box="[1164,1343,1579,1603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DA708B5F8F18FFF4FF60F98AFD620ABD" blockId="11.[151,1437,1649,2036]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FF60F98AFE0C0B9A" author="Maldonado, J." box="[199,407,1649,1676]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that Breddin’s description was insufficient to identify this species, but we disagree. 
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FF30F96EFEDE0BA6" author="Breddin, G." box="[151,325,1685,1712]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="147 - 148" refId="ref15054" refString="Breddin, G. (1904) Neue Rhynchotenausbeute aus Sud-Amerika. Societas Entomologica, 20, 147 - 148 + 153 - 154 + 177 - 178. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 9279381" type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin (1904)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FE64F96DFDF20BB9" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[451,617,1686,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FE64F96DFDF20BB9" box="[451,617,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: “...a dull black, broad animal, in which only a longitudinal band of the posterior lobe of the pronotum, along with its broad posterior margin and the slender spicules of the humeral angles, as well as the hemelytra, and a very narrow margin of the abdomen [connexivum], are somewhat dull light yellow.” Following Breddin’s description it is clear that this particular and striking color pattern, being mostly black with yellow hemelytra and black and yellow posterior pronotal lobe, is exactly the same as the color pattern described for 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FE2FF8B1FD190A75" authority="Maldonado" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[392,642,1865,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FE2FF8B1FE610A75" box="[392,506,1865,1892]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. bicolor</emphasis>
Maldonado
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="42F497DA8F18FFF4FD35F8B2FD770A72" box="[658,748,1865,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1543,1567]" captionTargetBox="[166,1435,309,1487]" captionTargetId="figure-84@11.[151,1435,309,1520]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view of Castolus type specimens. A. holotype of Castolus bicolor Maldonado, 1976 (synonym of C. nigriventris Breddin, 1904); B. holotype of C. bolivari Brailovsky, 1982; C. holotype labels of C. bicolor Maldonado, 1976." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556788/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). The only difference is that the pale areas in the 
<typeStatus id="057435FD8F18FFF4FABCF8B2FAE60A75" box="[1307,1405,1865,1891]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F18FFF4FF30F895FE920A91" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[151,265,1901,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F18FFF4FF30F895FE920A91" box="[151,265,1901,1928]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">C. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rather orange than yellow. Therefore, because of the same coloration patter between the two species, we synonymize Maldonado’s species under Breddin’s.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA708B5F8F18FFF3FF60F84EFC110DEF" blockId="11.[151,1437,1649,2036]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,430]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="550" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">
<bibRefCitation id="BE5EF6AE8F18FFF4FF60F84EFE020AC6" author="Maldonado, J." box="[199,409,1973,2000]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549" pagination="435 - 446" refId="ref15942" refString="Maldonado, J. (1976) Three new species of Castolus and a key to the species (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 78, 435 - 446. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 56099" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
also offered an intriguing observation, he mentioned that he had examined a female specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="A2D8CBCF8F18FFF4FEAAF822FEF70AE5" box="[269,364,2009,2035]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
with less extensive black areas on the pronotum, but otherwise very similar to the 
<typeStatus id="057435FD8F18FFF4FABCF822FAE60AE5" box="[1307,1405,2009,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="549">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F1FFFF3FF30FF6CFE910DA7" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[151,266,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F1FFFF3FF30FF6CFE910DA7" box="[151,266,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="550">C. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He hypothesized that this might be the female of the specimen he described. Unfortunately, he did not illustrate this specimen. Similar to what happens in 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F1FFFF3FD70FF40FCCB0DC3" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[727,848,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F1FFFF3FD70FF40FCCB0DC3" box="[727,848,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="550">C. lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species, some color variation might occur, with an extreme sexually dimorphic condition in 
<taxonomicName id="1DCFF0DC8F1FFFF3FD19FF24FCB10DEF" authority="Forero &amp; Mejía-Soto, 2021" authorityName="Forero &amp; Mejía-Soto" authorityYear="2021" box="[702,810,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Castolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F1FFFF3FD19FF24FCB10DEF" box="[702,810,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="550">C. rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E8BB574D8F1FFFF3FC96FF24FC110DEF" bold="true" box="[817,906,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="550">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F388EA368F1FFFF3FC96FF24FC110DEF" box="[817,906,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="550" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
